## Documentation File Size and Splitting

### Maximum File Size

**Rule: Keep documentation files between 150-300 lines maximum.**

- ✅ **150-200 lines** - Ideal for focused topics
- ✅ **200-250 lines** - Acceptable for comprehensive topics
- ⚠️ **250-300 lines** - Maximum acceptable size
- ❌ **300+ lines** - **MUST split into multiple files**

### When to Split

Split large documentation files when:

1. **File exceeds 300 lines** - Hard to navigate and digest
2. **Multiple distinct topics** - Each topic can stand alone
3. **Different audiences** - API reference vs. conceptual explanations
4. **Different use cases** - Getting started vs. advanced patterns
5. **Different layers** - Auth layer vs. execution layer

### How to Split Logically

**Cluster related concepts together:**

- **By topic** - All engines together, all modules together, all expressions together
- **By audience** - Concepts vs. API reference vs. troubleshooting
- **By use case** - Getting started vs. advanced patterns
- **By layer** - Auth layer vs. execution layer vs. data layer

**Example splitting strategy:**

```
Before (928 lines):
├── README.md (everything)

After (split into focused files):
├── README.md (overview, architecture, navigation - ~150 lines)
├── engines.md (all engine descriptions - ~300 lines)
├── modules.md (module system - ~200 lines)
├── expressions.md (expression language - ~200 lines)
├── api-reference.md (API reference - ~150 lines)
└── patterns.md (patterns & troubleshooting - ~150 lines)
```

### Main README Structure

The main README should serve as a **navigation hub**:

```markdown
# Package Name

## Overview
[One sentence: What is this?]
[One paragraph: Why does it matter?]

## The Simple Version
[Analogy + basic example]

## Architecture
[High-level architecture diagram/explanation]

## Documentation Structure

This package documentation is organized into focused topics:

- **[engines.md](./engines.md)** - Detailed engine descriptions
- **[modules.md](./modules.md)** - Module system and custom modules
- **[expressions.md](./expressions.md)** - MaiaScript expression language
- **[api-reference.md](./api-reference.md)** - Complete API reference
- **[patterns.md](./patterns.md)** - Common patterns and troubleshooting

## Quick Start

[Simple example showing basic usage]

## Related Documentation

- [Link to related packages]
- [Link to architecture docs]
```

**Key principles:**
- ✅ Keep main README concise (~150 lines max)
- ✅ Provide clear navigation to sub-files
- ✅ Include quick start example
- ✅ Link to related documentation

### Sub-File Structure

Each sub-file should be **self-contained** but link to related files:

```markdown
# Topic Name

## Overview
[Brief overview of this specific topic]

## [Main Content]
[Detailed explanation]

## Related Topics

- [Link to related sub-file]
- [Link back to main README]

## See Also

- [Link to related package docs]
```

**Key principles:**
- ✅ Each file focuses on one topic (250-300 lines max)
- ✅ Include overview section
- ✅ Link to related files for context
- ✅ Cross-reference related concepts

### Logical Clustering Examples

**✅ Good Clustering:**

```
maia-script/
├── README.md (overview + navigation)
├── engines.md (all 10 engines together)
├── modules.md (module system + custom modules)
├── expressions.md (expression language reference)
├── api-reference.md (complete API)
└── patterns.md (patterns + troubleshooting)
```

**❌ Bad Clustering:**

```
maia-script/
├── README.md (overview)
├── engine-1.md (single engine)
├── engine-2.md (single engine)
├── engine-3.md (single engine)
... (10 separate files - too fragmented)
```

**Why:** Engines are related concepts that belong together. Split only when a single topic exceeds 300 lines.

### Cross-References

**Always include cross-references:**

- Main README → Links to all sub-files
- Sub-files → Link back to main README
- Sub-files → Link to related sub-files
- Sub-files → Link to related package docs

**Example:**

```markdown
## Related Documentation

- [Main README](./README.md) - Package overview
- [engines.md](./engines.md) - Engine details
- [expressions.md](./expressions.md) - Expression language
- [Boot / loader docs](../02_maia-loader/README.md) - `@MaiaOS/runtime` (same doc folder; source in `libs/maia-runtime`)
```

### File Naming Conventions

Use clear, descriptive names:

- ✅ `engines.md` - Clear topic name
- ✅ `api-reference.md` - Standard naming
- ✅ `auth-layer.md` - Descriptive layer name
- ❌ `part1.md` - Not descriptive
- ❌ `details.md` - Too vague

### Summary

**File Size Rules:**
- 150-200 lines: Ideal
- 200-250 lines: Acceptable
- 250-300 lines: Maximum
- 300+ lines: **MUST split**

**Splitting Strategy:**
- Cluster by topic, audience, use case, or layer
- Main README = Navigation hub (~150 lines)
- Sub-files = Focused topics (250-300 lines max)
- Include cross-references between files

