## Terminology Consistency

### Create a Glossary

For each major concept area, maintain consistent terminology:

**CoValues:**
- ✅ "CoValue" (capital C, capital V)
- ✅ "CoMap", "CoList", "CoStream" (capital C, capital letter for type)
- ❌ "co-value", "coValue", "co_map"

**Actors:**
- ✅ "actor" (lowercase when referring to concept)
- ✅ "Actor" (capitalized when referring to the class/type)
- ✅ "actor definition" (lowercase)

**Schemas:**
- ✅ "schema" (lowercase)
- ✅ "Schema" (capitalized when referring to the system)
- ✅ "$schema" (with dollar sign when referring to JSON Schema field)

### Document Your Choices

In each doc, establish terminology early:

```markdown
## Terminology

In this document:
- **CoValue** refers to any collaborative data structure (CoMap, CoList, etc.)
- **actor** refers to a MaiaOS component definition
- **schema** refers to a JSON Schema definition
```

